1
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:15,640
Kluay.

2
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:40,200
Here.

3
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:45,520
Feel better now that you dragged me out?

4
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:47,920
Please have some sympathy for them.

5
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,920
And you're not a heartless person anyway.

6
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,600
Even if I hadn't pulled you out,
you wouldn't have stayed yourself.

7
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:57,560
It was just a car accident.

8
00:02:58,160 --> 00:03:00,400
Oh please, listen to you talking.

9
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:03,280
When you heard
that Sin got into an accident,

10
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,960
your face went pale.

11
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,800
But he's safe now, right?

12
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:12,800
He should be fine now.
Do you want to go see him?

13
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:14,600
No need.

14
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:18,920
Then I hope he recovers quickly.

15
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:21,640
We have to go keep watch over Mr. Arnon.

16
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:23,520
I think it's too much of a coincidence.

17
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:27,280
Same hospital, rooms next to each other.

18
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:29,440
Both injured on the same night.

19
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:41,000
Maybe we should memorize
the room numbers and buy lottery tickets.

20
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:44,720
Not funny?

21
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,240
Oh.

22
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:48,120
Do you remember

23
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:51,000
the look on Jirasin's aunt's face

24
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:54,360
when she heard
Mr. Arnon got stabbed in that room?

25
00:03:56,480 --> 00:04:01,280
Yes. She was shocked. That's normal.

26
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,880
I don't think it was normal.

27
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:06,040
That woman interrogated us
way too obviously.

28
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:09,040
You mean she might

29
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:11,880
know something about what happened?

30
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:15,240
Not that much. But I feel like

31
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:17,800
I'm very familiar with that voice.

32
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:21,959
And it's like I've seen something
like that somewhere before.

33
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,920
Is he badly injured?

34
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,440
I feel like I've heard that voice

35
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:28,680
somewhere before,
I just can't remember where.

36
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:33,040
It might just be déjà vu.

37
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:35,680
That happens to people all the time.

38
00:04:36,520 --> 00:04:37,640
It's more than that.

39
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,800
I think we should go talk inside the room.

40
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:45,280
Talking about her
right in front of their room

41
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,640
isn't appropriate. Let's go.

42
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:48,720
Come on.

43
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,200
Som.

44
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:58,760
Hello.

45
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,200
Kluay?

46
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:10,760
Yes, that's right.

47
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:13,200
What was he thinking,
arranging the police matter for me?

48
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:16,320
It's better to let Uncle Rut handle it.

49
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:19,400
Besides, they're all friends.
It'll progress faster.

50
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,960
And the reason I'm like this,

51
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:23,360
isn't it because of his good guy Warat?

52
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,400
Sin.

53
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,600
Don't let him step into this room again.

54
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,160
That includes Arnon.

55
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:35,600
If you see them wheeling his corpse out,
don't forget to tell me.

56
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:37,520
I'll go pour sacred water for him.

57
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:40,840
Then… I think

58
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:43,240
we should change rooms, Sin.

59
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,640
Why change? Why should we?

60
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:49,440
Well, I see that
you don't want to be near them.

61
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:51,960
Maybe we should move farther away?

62
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:54,920
Not wanting to see them
doesn't mean I have to run away.

63
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:58,280
Well… I…

64
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:01,160
I'm worried about Uncle Rut. I mean…

65
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:06,080
I feel the same as you. I'm afraid that

66
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:09,120
if Uncle Rut stays too close to Warat,

67
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:11,400
there'll be trouble again.

68
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:14,240
Besides,
Warat is already suspicious of Uncle Rut.

69
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,960
Serves him right.

70
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:19,560
Wasn't he the one
sneaking around to see Warat?

71
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:23,000
Now he's suspected of being a stalker.

72
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:24,800
Serves him right.

73
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:29,200
It's not my job to clean up after him.

74
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:31,360
Shut your mouth, Sin.

75
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:35,560
If you don't,
I'll shove these documents into it.

76
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:38,640
I'm helping you here,
getting these papers sorted for you.

77
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:41,120
Who asked you to?
You volunteered. Why complain now?

78
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:43,080
I'm helping you, Sin!

79
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:45,040
Stop it, please.

80
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:47,120
I'm begging you.

81
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,840
Sin isn't well.

82
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:51,880
You're the same, Anong.

83
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:54,280
Don't think I'm only
upset with your nephew.

84
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:57,320
You've been doing things
behind my back too.

85
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:59,480
I warned you before

86
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,840
not to do anything behind my back again.

87
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:03,840
What?

88
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,920
What did I do to you?

89
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,200
What did you do?

90
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:10,080
This.

91
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,120
What is this?

92
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:14,120
I'm asking you, what is this?!

93
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,880
Don't shout at my aunt!

94
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,720
Stay out of it. The grown-ups are talking!

95
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:18,800
Sin, Sin.

96
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:20,720
Sin.

97
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:23,440
I'll handle it myself.

98
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:41,520
Oh, Det. Didn't you say you'd just
come down to check the site briefly?

99
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:45,400
I've called you so many times.
You didn't pick up once. Ugh.

100
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:51,760
Alright.

101
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:54,200
So you really want
to pick a fight with me?

102
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:04,880
It's me.

103
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:07,120
You're Ms. Ameena, right?

104
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,400
Of course I am.

105
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:14,640
Uh, why is

106
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,400
your face…

107
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:20,040
My face? What about it?
What's wrong with my face?

108
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:21,680
Oh.

109
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:24,480
Why is something happening to everyone?

110
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:27,320
Both Mr. Sin and Mr. Arnon,
and now you too, Ms. Ameena.

111
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,680
Did you get into a fight with someone?

112
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:32,640
Are you crazy? I just had injections done.

113
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:35,440
Oh, injections.

114
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:37,559
Then I'm sorry. Injections.

115
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:41,600
By the way, what did you mean
by saying everyone's in trouble?

116
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,080
What happened?

117
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:46,240
Wait, you don't know anything?

118
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:50,200
Here.

119
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,200
You little troublemaker.

120
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:54,920
You took Ms. Ameena to the morgue?

121
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,960
She deserved it.
That woman loves to meddle.

122
00:08:58,040 --> 00:09:00,440
Good thing my hands were full of things.

123
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:02,800
Otherwise, it would've been much worse.

124
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:06,320
Maybe Ms. Ameena
came to visit you, Mr. Arnon?

125
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:08,560
They're in totally different circles.

126
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:11,280
- They're not that close.
- Oh?

127
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,960
Are you underestimating me?

128
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:17,280
Maybe she wants to get close to me.

129
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:18,920
Oh, really?

130
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:21,400
Great then.
I'll wheel your bed over there.

131
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:23,800
How about staying close with her
in the morgue? Wanna go?

132
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:26,520
Som, why are you
talking to Mr. Arnon like that?

133
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,160
Oh, it's fine.

134
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:31,000
They say when a woman gets jealous,
it means she loves you.

135
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:33,160
Hey, Arnon.

136
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:35,720
Who said I'm jealous of you?

137
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:39,720
It's called being annoyed. Annoyed.

138
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:40,920
Not jealous at all.

139
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:44,000
You two are the same.

140
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:48,080
Then let Som look after Mr. Arnon for now.

141
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:50,120
Well, you made an appointment
with the police, right?

142
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,160
Do you want me to go down with you?

143
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:53,920
Of course I do.

144
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:58,080
You probably understand those documents
I got from the thieves better than I do.

145
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,240
So,

146
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:04,840
the reason the thieves broke
into Baan Saeng Wan Mai was for documents?

147
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:09,520
You want to know? Come down
and talk to them with me. Come on.

148
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:12,480
Alright.

149
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:14,600
Be right back.

150
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:34,800
That room is just
a general document storage room.

151
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,640
There's nothing valuable in there, right?

152
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:39,160
Yes.

153
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:43,520
But even if it were
the reception room or Mama Toi's office,

154
00:10:44,040 --> 00:10:47,080
there's nothing valuable
in Baan Saeng Wan Mai.

155
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:50,040
But the word "valuable"

156
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:52,520
doesn't mean the same thing
to everyone, Kluay.

157
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,280
Oh.

158
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:55,680
You're right.

159
00:10:56,200 --> 00:11:00,200
But the children's name records
that the thief tried to steal,

160
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:03,520
no matter how I think about it,
I can't figure out

161
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,480
who they'd be valuable to.

162
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:09,080
Maybe it's some kind
of discrediting scheme.

163
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:10,320
Is it possible?

164
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:13,800
Does Baan Saeng Wan Mai
or your mom have any competitors

165
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:15,400
or enemies?

166
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,680
Kluay, Kluay.

167
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,760
Kluay, Kluay.

168
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,360
Come on.

169
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:39,600
I feel bad seeing you make that face.

170
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:43,000
I think
we should leave this place quickly.

171
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:50,320
Mr. Warat, are you okay?

172
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:53,760
Are there really that many?

173
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:57,320
Yes.

174
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:00,600
I knew it.

175
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,800
Coming to a hospital,

176
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:05,880
you're bound to see a lot.
I tried not to say it.

177
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:07,280
But you still ran into them.

178
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:12,000
Right now, I can't move my legs.

179
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:14,760
But we have to keep going.
Come on, I'll carry you.

180
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:16,520
Hey, how can you do that?

181
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:19,800
People will think I'm sick
and take me to the emergency room.

182
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:24,440
From what you see,

183
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:26,760
no one's asking for help, right?

184
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:28,280
No.

185
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,400
Just…

186
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:34,480
saying hi, that's all.

187
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:35,720
Hi.

188
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:44,120
Oh, Kluay.

189
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:45,480
- Huh?
- I've got an idea.

190
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:47,400
Close your eyes.

191
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:50,680
See? Once you close your eyes,

192
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:52,120
you don't see anything.

193
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:54,400
- Am I smart?
- Yes.

194
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:56,880
But

195
00:12:57,480 --> 00:13:00,960
I think the train
doesn't have just the two of us anymore.

196
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:07,040
I feel something heavy on my shoulders.

197
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:11,680
This train is getting too heavy.

198
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:15,240
Yes. Ugh.

199
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:16,800
Are we far along?

200
00:13:20,880 --> 00:13:22,160
Kluay.

201
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:24,200
We're almost at the elevator.

202
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:28,200
Everyone, let's stop the fun here.

203
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:32,000
If you all squeeze into the elevator,
there won't be any way out.

204
00:13:34,920 --> 00:13:37,040
- Oh.
- Are they all gone?

205
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:41,800
Yes, all gone.

206
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:43,760
Okay.

207
00:13:58,240 --> 00:13:59,520
The elevator's very empty.

208
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:04,400
Very empty.

209
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:07,800
Let's get out of here. Oh. Hey.

210
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:24,880
Kluay.

211
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:27,440
I don't know if you're really asleep

212
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:30,040
or pretending to avoid me.

213
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:36,840
But I'll sit here

214
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:38,560
until you agree to talk to me.

215
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:44,120
Since the day Ameena hurt you,

216
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:46,400
I've never been happy.

217
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:49,440
I truly want to apologize
from the bottom of my heart.

218
00:14:50,280 --> 00:14:51,880
But I never had the chance.

219
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:55,200
I'm really glad

220
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:58,280
that now I can be close to you again.

221
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:04,280
Even though it hurts so much

222
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:06,960
to see you this sick.

223
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:11,720
Can we be friends again?

224
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:17,360
I will make up for

225
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:20,160
everything that destroyed your life.

226
00:15:21,280 --> 00:15:22,400
Please give me a chance.

227
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,080
Kluay.

228
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:47,440
Det.

229
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:49,440
What are you doing?

230
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:52,920
I always thought you were weird,

231
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:55,520
but never thought you'd mess
with someone close like this.

232
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:08,640
Still not working yet?

233
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:12,720
Not at all.

234
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:16,560
Hey.

235
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:18,680
Just tell me.

236
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:21,600
- How are they?
- Uh.

237
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:24,800
You're better not knowing.

238
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:27,440
The elevator's about to arrive.

239
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:52,480
If you're scared, why do you need
to look there? Look at me.

240
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:55,000
Uh…

241
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:58,640
And who's watching the elevator?
We might miss it.

242
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:05,319
We won't miss it.
We're almost there. One more floor.

243
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:25,560
Wait.

244
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:27,720
Again?

245
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:29,960
Hey.

246
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:33,440
Hey, I'm starting to lose it.
What exactly do you want?

247
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:37,920
Mr. Warat. Mr. Warat.

248
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:40,040
She moved over here.

249
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:43,720
Where they are doesn't matter.
I'm talking to you.

250
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:45,080
What exactly do you want?

251
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:49,360
- Male or female?
- A mother with a baby.

252
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:52,880
Oh, a woman and a child.

253
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:56,640
I'm speaking nicely to you.

254
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,920
If you don't stop meddling with us,

255
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,960
I'll take action. I'm not threatening you.

256
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:06,000
- Are they gone yet?
- Not yet.

257
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:08,160
Mm.

258
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:11,080
Uh, can anyone hear us?

259
00:18:11,880 --> 00:18:13,520
We're stuck in the elevator.

260
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:14,720
Hello?

261
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:17,080
Hello?

262
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:23,320
What's this liquid?

263
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:27,120
She even brought a friend?

264
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,880
Hey.

265
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:30,560
Ew, what is this?

266
00:18:33,080 --> 00:18:34,680
It's lymph.

267
00:18:43,040 --> 00:18:44,920
So what exactly do you want, Anong?

268
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,880
Say it straight.
Stop beating around the bush.

269
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:50,440
And don't make excuses.

270
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:52,800
If I wanted to hear excuses,
I could just call you.

271
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:55,640
I don't need to sit here
acting stupid like this.

272
00:18:56,920 --> 00:19:00,560
I was foolishly happy,
thinking you came to visit Sin.

273
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:03,160
You're still
being sarcastic with me, Anong?

274
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:11,240
I don't feel like
I've done anything wrong.

275
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,760
I'm confident in the love

276
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:16,720
and loyalty I have for you.

277
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:20,600
Or do you think I'm not as I say I am?

278
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:25,960
Then say it.

279
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:28,200
Say that I don't love you,

280
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:30,800
that I don't take good care of you.

281
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:35,080
I know you take care of me.

282
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:38,440
But that's a different issue
from what I'm asking.

283
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:40,680
I want to know who this man is.

284
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:42,960
Huh?

285
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:47,280
I'm losing patience with you, Anong.

286
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:51,600
Fine.

287
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:54,920
Since you already think I'm wrong,

288
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:57,880
no matter what I say,
it'll just sound like excuses.

289
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:01,600
That's fine, Rut. Go ahead and scold me,

290
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:03,840
say whatever you want. Go on.

291
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:05,440
You're even

292
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:09,520
throwing yourself in to protect him?

293
00:20:11,120 --> 00:20:14,080
That means this man must be
very important to you, right?

294
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:18,560
I'll ask you one last time.

295
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:21,400
Who is this man?

296
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:30,680
Your choice. It's your choice, Anong.

297
00:20:33,520 --> 00:20:34,680
Fine.

298
00:20:36,160 --> 00:20:38,080
Then get ready to divorce me.

299
00:20:38,680 --> 00:20:42,000
Pack your things, along with Sin's,
and leave my house today.

300
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:46,320
No, you can't.
You can't, Mr. Rut. Mr. Rut.

301
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:47,240
- Mr. Rut.
- Let go!

302
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:52,560
A creditor?

303
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:56,520
That Kaew you were talking to on the phone
is your creditor?

304
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,960
Why, Anong?

305
00:21:00,680 --> 00:21:02,880
The money in the bank, the interest,

306
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:06,640
the shop rents and everything, I let you
handle all that. Wasn't that enough?

307
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:07,960
Not enough to spend?

308
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:12,120
Yes.

309
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:16,920
I went to…

310
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:20,480
I signed as a loan guarantor for a friend.

311
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:22,640
Why are you so stupid?

312
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:26,200
Who in their right mind signs as guarantor
for illegal loan sharks like that?

313
00:21:26,960 --> 00:21:29,080
You're stupid. Absolutely stupid.

314
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:32,640
I was stupid.

315
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:36,840
I was stupid and unlucky too.

316
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:40,440
Sin ended up like this,
and you don't even trust me.

317
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:45,640
I should just die. I should just die. Die.

318
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:47,360
I shouldn't even be alive.

319
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:50,720
That's enough, Anong. That's enough.

320
00:21:51,480 --> 00:21:52,320
This is embarrassing.

321
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:57,520
I think I've seen you
at a coffee shop before.

322
00:21:58,720 --> 00:22:00,400
Yes, that day

323
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:03,560
when Det brought that
"letter from hell" for Kluay,

324
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:05,560
and she got beaten up badly.

325
00:22:05,640 --> 00:22:07,640
- Oh.
- That's enough, Som.

326
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:09,600
I never wanted it to turn out like that.

327
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:13,680
I'm sorry for mistaking you for Kluay.

328
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:15,240
Uh, it's fine.

329
00:22:16,520 --> 00:22:18,520
Luckily, it was just holding hands,

330
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:21,120
not something like…

331
00:22:22,720 --> 00:22:24,200
Arnon.

332
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:25,920
Why are you being friendly to him?

333
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:29,200
He caused Kluay to be slapped and publicly
humiliated all over social media.

334
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:31,840
I feel sorry for him. He's clearly upset.

335
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:33,880
Arnon, shh.

336
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:35,400
Your boyfriend's really kind, Som.

337
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:38,800
Get well soon.

338
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:42,280
Sorry again for mistaking you for Kluay.

339
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,040
I'll go now, Som.

340
00:22:46,640 --> 00:22:48,520
And don't come see us again.

341
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:51,400
If Ameena finds out,
there'll be trouble again.

342
00:22:51,480 --> 00:22:54,560
Seriously, is it really this hard

343
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:56,440
to remove someone from your life?

344
00:22:58,600 --> 00:22:59,800
Just wait.

345
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:01,920
If Kluay comes up, I'm telling her

346
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:04,360
that you took his side, Arnon.

347
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:12,360
So you're really not
going to tell me what you want?

348
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:15,360
Her child.

349
00:23:16,040 --> 00:23:17,480
Ma'am.

350
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:21,720
It's not good for your child to stay
in the elevator this long, you know.

351
00:23:22,320 --> 00:23:25,680
The air isn't good. It affects the baby.

352
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:28,800
Hey.

353
00:23:29,320 --> 00:23:31,160
She's listening to you.

354
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:32,240
- Really?
- Yeah.

355
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:33,680
Keep going.

356
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:35,320
Ma'am,

357
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:39,600
if there's anything, you can tell Kluay.
She can communicate with you.

358
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:42,800
And I'll support everything.

359
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:45,000
Ah. Yes.

360
00:23:45,520 --> 00:23:48,560
The baby looks tired too. Poor thing.

361
00:23:48,640 --> 00:23:50,040
The baby probably wants to rest.

362
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:57,080
The baby must have just been born, right?

363
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:01,360
Looks very weak too.

364
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:03,800
- Kluay.
- Hm?

365
00:24:04,320 --> 00:24:06,600
That means she and her baby

366
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:08,880
must have been in this hospital before.

367
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:12,440
Probably sick or something.
What are they wearing?

368
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:16,640
The mother is wearing
this hospital's gown.

369
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:19,720
The baby has

370
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:21,840
a hospital blanket too.

371
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:26,040
- Hey.
- Oh?

372
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:28,080
Oh?

373
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:29,360
What?

374
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:30,640
PEDIATRICS DEPARTMENT

375
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:31,560
Look.

376
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:33,520
Pediatrics department.

377
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:34,600
PEDIATRICS DEPARTMENT

378
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:36,560
Uh…

379
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:38,800
So, what next?

380
00:24:38,880 --> 00:24:40,880
Tell her to press floor two.

381
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:43,160
The floor where she stayed most recently.

382
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:46,040
The last time…

383
00:24:46,560 --> 00:24:49,160
- The last time she was there.
- Oh, okay.

384
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:52,600
Oh?

385
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:54,280
She's gone.

386
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:58,720
Oh? She pressed it.

387
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:02,360
Um…

388
00:25:02,440 --> 00:25:07,480
She's thanking you.

389
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:10,160
Where is she?

390
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:13,680
She's right here.

391
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:24,800
Hey!

392
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:30,120
Hey.

393
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:47,280
Wave. Wave goodbye to her.

394
00:25:48,480 --> 00:25:49,440
Say goodbye.

395
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:51,200
Smile too.

396
00:25:52,560 --> 00:25:53,400
Smile.

397
00:26:01,520 --> 00:26:02,840
They're really all gone?

398
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:05,600
Yes, both of them.

399
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:07,600
- The mother and baby?
- Yes.

400
00:26:07,680 --> 00:26:09,240
That means…

401
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:13,280
The liquid you saw earlier

402
00:26:13,360 --> 00:26:15,200
was lymph.

403
00:26:17,160 --> 00:26:18,600
Wait for me.

404
00:26:23,720 --> 00:26:27,160
Oh, you're all here together.

405
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:30,520
Ameena, get out.

406
00:26:31,120 --> 00:26:34,200
Who are you to order me?
Is this elevator yours?

407
00:26:38,920 --> 00:26:40,240
What's this liquid?

408
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:43,160
Huh?

409
00:26:56,800 --> 00:27:00,160
What is it? It smells too.

410
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:04,240
Ugh, it's bitter in my throat.

411
00:27:05,640 --> 00:27:07,920
- What is this?!
- The liquid from earlier…

412
00:27:08,920 --> 00:27:10,240
Yes.

413
00:27:10,320 --> 00:27:12,960
Aren't you going to check on her?

414
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:15,800
- No. I'm not that good of a person. Go.
- Mr. Warat.

415
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:19,880
BOONYAVEJ HOSPITAL

416
00:27:19,960 --> 00:27:22,560
Actually, I can go talk
at the police station,

417
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:24,680
so you don't
have to come all the way here.

418
00:27:24,760 --> 00:27:27,440
Oh. I have to take
Mr. Arnon's statement anyway.

419
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:30,440
Oh right, I forgot.

420
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:31,400
Hello.

421
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:33,000
Please have a seat.

422
00:27:34,120 --> 00:27:35,040
Alright.

423
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:40,400
What are these documents?
You can explain, Ms. Kluay.

424
00:27:42,040 --> 00:27:43,760
We'll just talk casually.

425
00:27:43,840 --> 00:27:46,240
I'll record everything officially.

426
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:47,840
Alright.

427
00:27:48,760 --> 00:27:49,800
Uh.

428
00:27:49,880 --> 00:27:51,160
PERSONAL INFORMATION

429
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:54,760
Are these the documents
you got back from the thief?

430
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,240
Yes. All of them.

431
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:04,920
They're the list of children
from Baan Saeng Wan Mai.

432
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:08,920
We have to submit this
to the central authority every year, but

433
00:28:09,880 --> 00:28:12,120
these are from many years ago.

434
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:14,640
Have you ever encountered
a case like this, officer?

435
00:28:14,720 --> 00:28:17,920
Stealing items or documents from

436
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:20,640
an orphanage. I think it's strange.

437
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:26,080
But it's possible that orphanages
have financial interests involved.

438
00:28:26,160 --> 00:28:28,000
We're not ruling that out.

439
00:28:29,320 --> 00:28:30,280
What about the gun?

440
00:28:30,360 --> 00:28:32,240
Did the thief have a gun?

441
00:28:32,760 --> 00:28:35,080
Were they really planning to harm us?

442
00:28:35,680 --> 00:28:38,560
I didn't tell you because
I was afraid you'd react like this.

443
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:41,480
It was a homemade gun.
No registered owner.

444
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:43,080
No license.

445
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:46,000
But this case isn't easy.

446
00:28:46,080 --> 00:28:49,360
Did you get any fingerprints?

447
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,160
The suspect was wearing gloves.

448
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:54,760
The key issue seems to be the list
of names from Baan Saeng Wan Mai, Kluay.

449
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:04,440
Sorry, I didn't order anything.

450
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:07,560
Yes, everything
has been delivered to Mr. Sin's room.

451
00:29:11,240 --> 00:29:13,800
One moment, please.
It's an overseas call from Taiwan.

452
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,120
Hello.

453
00:29:23,040 --> 00:29:24,920
Oh… Mom?

454
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:27,720
I…

455
00:29:28,240 --> 00:29:30,680
I know you're in a meeting over there.

456
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:35,360
I'm not seriously hurt.
I'll be able to return to work soon.

457
00:29:36,040 --> 00:29:39,480
Thank you very much to you and Mr. Supol.

458
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:41,440
Yes.

459
00:29:47,320 --> 00:29:50,840
The Chairwoman really went all out.

460
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:53,320
Are you going to eat now?

461
00:29:54,520 --> 00:29:56,360
It's fine. Go ahead.

462
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:58,040
I suppose it's a good omen

463
00:29:59,480 --> 00:30:01,120
that she isn't angry with me.

464
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:05,520
Don't relax too soon.
It always starts like that.

465
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:09,040
But when the Chairwoman heard
you were in an accident,

466
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:11,400
she softened up, as you can see.

467
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:13,720
Mom is overseas.

468
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:17,800
I didn't tell anyone. How did she know?

469
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:24,640
You're unbelievable.

470
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:28,200
I won't let the work I've pushed
almost to completion

471
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:33,000
collapse because of small loopholes
that Mr. Warat used to corner us.

472
00:30:34,160 --> 00:30:36,800
If you had been this clear from the start,

473
00:30:37,320 --> 00:30:38,920
I wouldn't have ended up like this.

474
00:30:41,240 --> 00:30:43,160
How is that my fault?

475
00:30:45,160 --> 00:30:46,160
That's true.

476
00:30:47,640 --> 00:30:48,760
It's not yours.

477
00:30:52,520 --> 00:30:53,560
It's Warat's.

478
00:30:54,160 --> 00:30:55,520
Exactly.

479
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:59,680
Oh, by the way, I ran into Ms. Ameena too.
She said she was coming to visit you.

480
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:01,920
No one came.

481
00:31:05,920 --> 00:31:08,080
- Where are you?
<i>- What do you mean where am I?</i>

482
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:10,440
I'm at home, of course.

483
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,760
Then why didn't you call me?

484
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:14,840
<i>Okay, okay.</i>

485
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:17,600
I'll hurry back.
I just have a little work left.

486
00:31:18,640 --> 00:31:20,520
Work? What work?

487
00:31:21,320 --> 00:31:24,680
I already know you're home.
I'll finish up and head back. That's it.

488
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:29,320
Hey. I asked what work.
Can't you tell me, Det?

489
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:30,280
<i>Det,</i>

490
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:32,240
hello?

491
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:01,280
Where are you going? Come here.

492
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:15,240
It's not like that, Kluay.
It's not what you think.

493
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:18,840
Oh! A man in the women's restroom!

494
00:32:18,920 --> 00:32:22,040
- How did he get in here?
- Get out of here right now!

495
00:32:22,120 --> 00:32:24,680
- This is the women's restroom.
- How did you get in here?

496
00:32:24,760 --> 00:32:28,040
- This is the women's restroom.
- How did you get in here?

497
00:32:28,120 --> 00:32:29,880
You pervert! How did you get in here?

498
00:32:29,960 --> 00:32:31,520
Get out now!

499
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:34,800
I'm sorry. My friend just…

500
00:32:35,320 --> 00:32:37,080
Ugh, just go outside!

501
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:50,320
Why is she in the restroom so long?

502
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:55,160
Diarrhea?

503
00:32:58,080 --> 00:33:00,960
Thank you, Kluay, for helping me.

504
00:33:01,040 --> 00:33:04,720
I had to help. What were you thinking,
going into the women's restroom?

505
00:33:05,240 --> 00:33:08,760
I told you, it wasn't intentional.
Will you ever believe me?

506
00:33:10,600 --> 00:33:11,640
No.

507
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:15,720
You know the trust I had in you
ran out a long time ago.

508
00:33:16,440 --> 00:33:19,800
Please. Let this be
the last time we see each other.

509
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:21,520
Wait.

510
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:24,840
It wasn't easy for me to meet you again.
Listen to my explanation.

511
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:27,160
Det, Ameena's around here.

512
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:28,680
Can you stop causing trouble for me?

513
00:33:28,760 --> 00:33:30,120
Ameena already left.

514
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:31,880
Then you should let me go even more.

515
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:34,960
Because you're like this,
always doing things behind Ameena's back.

516
00:33:35,040 --> 00:33:37,000
That's why things never end peacefully.

517
00:33:37,600 --> 00:33:41,360
This will be the last time
if you listen and let me explain.

518
00:33:41,440 --> 00:33:42,840
Then let go of me first.

519
00:33:44,640 --> 00:33:45,480
Exactly.

520
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:48,120
Holding someone else's
girlfriend's hand like that

521
00:33:49,240 --> 00:33:50,800
isn't good, Det.

522
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:52,680
You should leave.

523
00:33:52,760 --> 00:33:56,120
How can he leave? Aren't you
going to let me greet him, babe?

524
00:34:01,120 --> 00:34:03,200
Nice to finally meet you properly.

525
00:34:03,720 --> 00:34:04,880
Detboworn.

526
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:06,160
Detbodin.

527
00:34:07,360 --> 00:34:09,360
Your name's so nice I forgot it.

528
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:12,880
- Take your hand off. We're not that close.
- Hey.

529
00:34:14,199 --> 00:34:15,159
Really? I thought

530
00:34:15,239 --> 00:34:18,480
my girlfriend's best friend
was like my best friend.

531
00:34:18,560 --> 00:34:21,719
Oh, is this the one, babe?
The one who got you slapped?

532
00:34:21,800 --> 00:34:24,719
The one who got you humiliated? Is it him?

533
00:34:26,639 --> 00:34:28,159
I didn't want things to turn out that way.

534
00:34:28,239 --> 00:34:30,360
Then how did you want it to turn out?

535
00:34:30,960 --> 00:34:34,679
Like this? Holding
someone else's girlfriend's hand?

536
00:34:34,760 --> 00:34:37,280
That's not true. I've never done that.

537
00:34:37,360 --> 00:34:39,320
At least just now you did.

538
00:34:41,520 --> 00:34:43,159
I'm warning you.

539
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:47,440
Stop meddling with Kluay,
and I'll let you go.

540
00:34:50,199 --> 00:34:53,719
Who do you think you are?
You're not the hospital owner.

541
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:54,880
What right do you have to threaten me?

542
00:34:55,480 --> 00:34:58,320
And don't tell me
you're Kluay's boyfriend.

543
00:34:58,840 --> 00:35:01,560
Save that for kids. Kluay and I

544
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:04,600
dated for a long time.
I can tell just by looking into her eyes

545
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:06,640
that she

546
00:35:08,200 --> 00:35:10,400
would never choose someone like you.

547
00:35:15,600 --> 00:35:17,200
Stop insulting my boyfriend, Det.

548
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:19,560
- That's not true.
- It is.

549
00:35:20,560 --> 00:35:22,040
He's my boyfriend.

550
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:23,000
I don't believe it.

551
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:25,400
If you want to push me
out of your life this badly,

552
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:28,760
just tell me directly.
You don't have to go this far.

553
00:35:28,840 --> 00:35:30,400
If I knew you despised me this much…

554
00:35:30,480 --> 00:35:32,560
I… I don't despise you, Det.

555
00:35:32,640 --> 00:35:35,360
- I just…
- Her despising you is reasonable.

556
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:37,440
If you get it, then go.

557
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:41,520
- It's not like that. It's… Hey.
- Why isn't it, babe?

558
00:35:41,600 --> 00:35:42,480
Hey.

559
00:35:55,520 --> 00:35:58,560
There's nothing more to talk about.
I'm leaving, Kluay.

560
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:20,680
Where have you been, Anong?

561
00:36:21,520 --> 00:36:25,120
You said you were just going
to buy something for Sin.

562
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:29,760
Anong.

563
00:36:30,280 --> 00:36:32,040
I'm asking you. Why aren't you answering?

564
00:36:33,760 --> 00:36:34,640
Anong.

565
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:37,200
What happened to you?

566
00:36:41,440 --> 00:36:42,360
Anong.

567
00:36:43,280 --> 00:36:45,240
Who did this to you? Tell me.

568
00:36:46,720 --> 00:36:47,640
They did.

569
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:52,880
They came to collect the debt.

570
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:56,320
NEXT EPISODE

571
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:57,920
<i>I begged for my life,</i>

572
00:36:58,000 --> 00:36:59,640
<i>bowed and pleaded.</i>

573
00:36:59,720 --> 00:37:02,400
<i>But they wouldn't listen.</i>

574
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:05,320
I'm worried about Kluay's safety.

575
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:09,000
Then we need to hurry
and find out who's behind that thief.

576
00:37:10,040 --> 00:37:12,960
If I'd known it would escalate like this,

577
00:37:13,040 --> 00:37:15,680
I wouldn't have dug into Kluay's past.

578
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:18,560
Sin.

579
00:37:23,760 --> 00:37:25,840
Mom and I are here to visit you.

580
00:37:28,800 --> 00:37:31,040
My hands are already dirty.

581
00:37:31,120 --> 00:37:33,480
A little more won't matter.

582
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:37,960
Mr. Warat.

583
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:39,000
Don't.

584
00:37:40,880 --> 00:37:41,720
Mr. Warat.

585
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:44,880
Why are you looking at me like that?

586
00:40:08,440 --> 00:40:10,600
Subtitle translator by: Panuwat Baikeawon
